delete from public.prompts;

-- Stil 1: Yatık poz — yüzük yere yatırılmış, önden ve hafif üstten çekim
-- Note: {{ENGRAVING}} placeholder is replaced by server action with user's custom text
insert into public.prompts (name, description, template, reference_image_url, category, sort_order) values
  (
    'Stil 1',
    'Yüzük yere yatırılmış, önden çekim',
    'Professional high-end e-commerce product photograph of a ring. MANDATORY POSE: The ring MUST be lying flat on its side horizontally on the surface, with the shank (band) facing upward. The ring is NOT standing upright — it is laid down, resting on its side. The shank curves upward like an arch viewed from the front. The camera is positioned at the front of the ring at nearly the same level, facing the decorative front face directly. There is only a very slight upward camera elevation — just enough to peek through the band opening and reveal the inside of the shank. The front face with all stones and design details faces the camera head-on. DO NOT stand the ring upright. DO NOT show the ring vertical. The ring is horizontal, flat, laying on the surface. {{ENGRAVING}}

Preserve every original design detail exactly: stone count, stone arrangement, prong placement, metal color variations including gold, rose gold, white gold, and any two-tone or multi-tone finishes must remain identical to the original. Geometric patterns, filigree work, and all structural elements must be perfectly preserved without any modification. Do not reproduce, show, or include any original text, stamps, hallmarks, or engravings that exist on the original product. CRITICAL: The proportional size ratio between the head (setting/stone area) and the band (shank) MUST remain exactly as in the original. DO NOT make the head larger or smaller relative to the band. DO NOT make the band thicker or thinner relative to the head. The overall scale relationship between all parts of the ring must be identical to the original product. The band cross-section profile and thickness MUST be preserved exactly as in the original — the band must not appear thinner, thicker, flatter, or rounder than the original regardless of viewing angle.

High-end jewelry retouching: ALL metal surfaces on the entire ring must be absolutely flawless, perfectly smooth, and mirror-polished — this includes the band exterior, band interior, AND every metal surface in the head and setting area: prongs, bezels, pavé channels, gallery walls, bridge work, cathedral shoulders, halo frames, and all metal surfaces between and around stones. Every metal area must have the exact same flawless, smooth, polished quality as the band exterior — no area should appear rougher, more textured, or less polished than any other. No visible pitting, porosity, casting marks, grain texture, orange peel texture, or any surface roughness whatsoever anywhere on the ring. No scratches, no dust particles, no fingerprints, no surface imperfections of any kind. Reflections on the metal must be soft, smooth, and gently diffused — NOT sharp or high-contrast. Close-range reflections must blend smoothly into the surface without creating the illusion of bumps, dents, or texture. Avoid harsh specular highlights that mimic surface imperfections. The environment reflected on the metal surfaces must also appear perfectly smooth and clean — no rough, textured, stone-like, or granular surfaces should be visible in any reflection. All reflections must show only a smooth, clean, featureless studio environment. The metal must look like it has been professionally polished and retouched to an immaculate, flawless finish. Preserve intentional micro-textures ONLY if they exist in the original design, such as satin finishes, hammered textures, brushed metal details, or matte sections — but even these must appear clean and deliberate, not rough or accidental.

If the ring contains stones or gems: each stone must look like a real, high-quality precious or semi-precious stone photographed with a macro lens in a professional studio. Each individual facet must be razor-sharp, geometrically precise, and distinctly visible. Stones must exhibit natural brilliance with bright internal light return, visible depth and transparency. The facet junctions must be crisp clean lines, not soft or blurred. Stones must have the unmistakable wet, glassy, alive quality of real cut stones — never dull, flat, frosted, or matte. CRITICAL: Preserve the exact original stone color, material, type, cut, shape, facet pattern, appearance, count, size, and setting without any alteration. If the original stone is a diamond, it MUST remain a diamond. If it is a colored gemstone (sapphire, ruby, emerald, etc.), it MUST remain that exact color and type. If the original stone is round brilliant, it MUST remain round brilliant. If princess cut, emerald cut, marquise, oval, pear, cushion, or any other cut — it MUST stay exactly the same. DO NOT change, replace, or alter the stone cut, shape, color, or material in any way. If the ring has NO stones, DO NOT add any stones — keep the ring plain as in the original.

Lighting: professional dual-source soft studio lighting with carefully controlled specular highlights that reveal three-dimensional form and surface quality. Subtle rim light separating the subject from the background. No lens flare, no glare, no artificial sparkle or glitter effects, no light leaks, no bokeh.

Full depth of field with every element in tack-sharp focus from front to back. No chromatic aberration, no color cast, no vignetting, no barrel distortion.

Background: clean pure white studio backdrop. Very subtle, natural contact shadow where the ring meets the surface, soft and diffused. No reflective floor, no mirrored surface, no gradient, no colored tint.

Shot with a Canon EOS R5 and Canon RF 100mm f/2.8L Macro IS USM lens. RAW file processed in Capture One with professional color grading for luxury e-commerce. The image must be absolutely indistinguishable from a real studio photograph — real optical properties, real light physics, real material behavior. Metal must reflect the studio environment naturally with subtle warm and cool tones in the reflections. Surfaces must show real-world material properties: the natural weight and presence of actual precious metal, not a digitally generated surface. No perfectly uniform gradients on metal — real polished gold and platinum have organic, flowing reflections with subtle variation. No synthetic or plastic-like appearance anywhere. No CGI look, no 3D render aesthetic, no digital illustration style, no video game graphics. No oversaturated colors, no HDR artifacts, no color banding, no posterization. No watermark, no text overlay, no logo, no border, no frame. No extra elements added, no stones removed, no design alterations of any kind.',
    null,
    'yüzük',
    1
  );

