insert into public.prompts (name, description, template, reference_image_url, category, sort_order) values
  (
    'Stil 1',
    'Kolye düz, eliptik kılavuz çizgisine oturtulmuş',
    'Professional high-end e-commerce product photograph of a necklace. The input consists of multiple reference images:
- Image 1 (pose_reference): A reference image showing a necklace floating in a perfect elliptical/oval shape on a clean white background. This defines the EXACT geometric layout, pose, and spatial arrangement the final necklace must follow.
- Image 2 (necklace_general_image): The complete overall view of the necklace — use this as the primary product reference for the entire piece.
- Image 3 (necklace_pendant_image): Close-up detail of the pendant, charm, or centerpiece.
- Image 4 (necklace_chain_detail_image): Close-up of the chain links and texture.
- Image 5 (necklace_clasp_image): The clasp/closure mechanism.

CORE GEOMETRY & POSE: The final necklace MUST be shaped and positioned exactly like the necklace in Image 1. It must form a perfect, continuous elliptical or oval loop floating in the center of the frame on the pure white background. The pendant/centerpiece is at the very bottom center of the loop, facing the camera directly. The chain extends perfectly along the elliptical path upwards on both sides, joining at the clasp at the top center. The camera is positioned looking straight at the floating necklace.

Using ALL reference images, produce a single professional product photograph that accurately represents the complete necklace. 
CRITICAL ENFORCEMENTS:
1. NO SHADOWS (FLOATING): The necklace MUST appear entirely isolated and floating. There must be absolutely NO drop shadows, NO contact shadows, and NO ambient occlusion cast onto the background. The background must remain pure, uninterrupted white everywhere.
2. CHAIN TOPOLOGY: You MUST meticulously study Image 4 (chain detail) and Image 2. Replicate the EXACT type, shape, and thickness of the chain links. If there are alternating link types (e.g. one long oval link followed by three small round links), you MUST count them and perfectly replicate that exact mathematical sequence across the entire necklace. If the links are twisted, flattened, or faceted, replicate that exact structure.
3. CLASP ORIENTATION: You MUST study Image 5 (clasp). The clasp mechanism must be placed at the top center of the necklace. The opening/mouth of the clasp (the part that clicks open) MUST face downwards towards the pendant. 
4. NO TEXT/LETTERS: There must be absolutely NO letters, text, watermarks, or logos anywhere on the necklace, pendant, or background.
5. EXACT REPLICATION: Every detail from every reference image must be faithfully preserved — stone colors, metal finish, chain pattern, clasp design, pendant shape. DO NOT alter, simplify, or reinterpret any design element.

If the necklace contains stones or gems: each stone must look like a real, high-quality precious or semi-precious stone. Preserve the exact original stone color, material, type, cut, shape, and setting. If the necklace has NO stones, DO NOT add any.

High-end jewelry retouching: ALL metal surfaces must be absolutely flawless, perfectly smooth, and mirror-polished. No scratches, no dust, no fingerprints, no stains, no smudges. Reflections must be soft, bright, and gently diffused. CRITICAL: There must be NO black, dark, muddy, or dirty reflections anywhere on the metal. The entire necklace must be uniformly bright, evenly lit, and immaculately clean from end to end. 

Lighting: professional softbox studio lighting providing 100% even illumination across the entire piece. No harsh shadows on the product itself. No lens flare, no glare, no artificial sparkle. Every part of the chain, pendant, and clasp must be equally visible, bright, and exceptionally clear with consistent high-key lighting.

Background: clean pure white studio backdrop (RGB: 255, 255, 255). The product must be floating completely isolated with ZERO shadows cast onto the background. No reflective floor, no gradient, no colored tint.

Shot with a medium format Hasselblad H6D-100c and 120mm macro lens for absolute maximum clarity and microscopic detail. The image must be absolutely indistinguishable from a real world-class studio photograph, perfectly retouched to eliminate any dark environmental reflections or impurities.',
    null,
    'kolye',
    1
  );

